# =========================
# REPO: jumping-vpn-preview
# FILE: SECURITY.md
# =========================
# Security Policy

## Status

This project is a **research prototype** and NOT a production-ready VPN or security system.

## Scope

- Protocol is experimental
- Runtime behavior is evolving
- Cryptography is NOT finalized

## Reporting Issues

If you discover a vulnerability or protocol flaw:

- Open an issue (preferred)
- Or contact privately if sensitive

## Disclaimer

Do NOT use this project in production or security-critical environments.

---

# =========================
# REPO: jumping-vpn-preview
# FILE: CONTRIBUTING.md
# =========================
# Contributing

This project explores a **session-centric networking model**.

## Principles

- Continuity > convenience
- Invariants > hacks
- Explainability > hidden behavior

## Contributions welcome

- protocol design feedback
- edge cases
- invariant violations
- migration bugs
- runtime stability improvements

## Guidelines

- keep changes minimal
- explain WHY, not just WHAT
- do not break core invariants

---

# =========================
# REPO: jumping-vpn-preview
# FILE: ROADMAP.md
# =========================
# Roadmap

## Phase 1 — Continuity Demo
- session survives transport failure
- migration + authority transfer

## Phase 2 — Runtime Stabilization
- EWMA smoothing
- hysteresis
- confidence-based decisions

## Phase 3 — Transport Layer
- real UDP improvements
- QUIC integration

## Phase 4 — Protocol Formalization
- state machine spec
- packet-level documentation
- invariants documentation

## Phase 5 — System Evolution
- transport-independent sessions
- continuity-first networking stack

